OL,3,C'Thoroughly evil' man jailed for
OL,4,Cmurdering partner
OL,6,FPaying tribute to Olivia, her mum,
OL,7,FAstrid Wood, spoke of her "loving,
OL,8,Fhardworking and helpful" daughter
OL,9,Fwhose compassion sparked her interest
OL,10,Fin nature, particularly protecting
OL,11,Fsmall animals.
OL,13,F"I gave life to Olivia and no-one, no
OL,14,Fperson on this earth was allowed to
OL,15,Ftake her life away. She will never
OL,16,Fwalk through my front door again; I
OL,17,Fcannot hear her footsteps ever again.
OL,19,F"She gave me purpose. She was
OL,20,Fbeautiful and confident walking her
OL,21,Fpath, she knew where she wanted to be.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
